-----------TO SETUP----------------------
1.Install docker &  docker compose locally
2.From parent directory type : docker compose up -d
3.Above step should download images & setup containers
4.Open any mysql or sql IDE.Connect at hostname:3306 with credentials (root,password).Create schema with sql ready at ./relational/src/main/resources/schema.sql
5.Option, open rabbitmq management from browser at : http://hostname:15672 with credentials (guest , guest)
6.Option, open kibana from browser at : http://hostname:5601/app/kibana#/home?_g=()

-------------------TO RUN--------------------------
7.Run console app first (To create messaging queues on RabbitMQ).Two message queues are created : command & result
8.Run relational or elastic app.If both relational & elastic are running they compete for the message on queue 'command' only one receives it.
9.If run relational app (schema must be created first on mysql-server).
10.Else run elastic app
